title: [BUG] Compilation error when SkiaSharp.Views nuget is referenced in a macOS Xamarin.Mac full project
body:
**Description**
Reproduction steps:
- With Visual Studio for mac, create a new "Cocoa App"
- Open "Options / Build / General", then change target framework to "Xamarin.Mac full, .Net Framework 4.7.2"
- Open "Manage nuget packages", then add "SkiaSharp.Views" to project
- Rebuild solution

**Code**
This sample project can be used to reproduce the issue
https://github.com/Odirb/BugSkiaSharpViews


**Expected Behavior**
The project should compile without any error

**Actual Behavior**
The build output show that clang has failed with this error: "ld: framework not found OpenGLES"
